Copper cables worth around R80 000 were recovered from a taxi, on the N2 freeway, near Amanzimtoti, following a tip-off to police. According to ET Rapid Response, members of their tactical response team, were alterted at around 9 am on Friday that two men had been spotted with the Eskom-owned cables. They were reportedly headed to Durban in a minibus taxi. When the vehicle was pulled over, the stolen cable was found inside, wrapped in plastic. Two men were arrested in connection with the theft by the Umkomaas SAPS, who then conducted a follow-up operation, which lead to the arrest of a third person. Officers also recovered the equipment, which was allegedly used to remove the cables, and discovered where they were stolen from.